s:1268:"<p>In this course, you’ll learn how to bring your HTML pages to life using <strong>CSS (Cascading Style Sheets)</strong>. CSS controls the layout, colors, fonts, spacing, and overall look of a webpage. You'll explore the basic syntax of CSS, learn how to apply styles using selectors, and understand the <strong>box model</strong>, which forms the foundation of web layout. By the end of this course, you'll be able to style your HTML pages and create visually appealing static websites.</p>
<p>This section includes:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>🎥 <strong>Class Video</strong> – A visual explanation of core CSS concepts with live demonstrations</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>📝 <strong>Class Note</strong> – A summary guide covering key CSS topics and examples</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>🔗 <strong>Additional Reference Materials</strong> – Curated links to tutorials and documentation for deeper learning</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>📋 <strong>Assignment</strong> – A hands-on task to practice styling an existing HTML page</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>❓ <strong>Quiz</strong> – A short evaluation to test and reinforce your understanding</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p>Use this course to gain practical styling skills and get one step closer to building professional-looking websites.</p>";